modules.name: AWS.Athena
modules.comments:
Amazon Athena is an interactive query service that lets you use standard SQL to analyze data directly in Amazon S3. You can point Athena at your data in Amazon S3 and run ad-hoc queries and get results in seconds. Athena is serverless, so there is no infrastructure to set up or manage. You pay only for the queries you run. Athena scales automatically—executing queries in parallel—so results are fast, even with large datasets and complex queries. For more information, see What is Amazon Athena in the Amazon Athena User Guide.

For code samples using the AWS SDK for Java, see Examples and Code Samples in the Amazon Athena User Guide.

declarations.comments: Returns the details of a single named query or a list of up to 50 queries, which you provide as an array of query ID strings. Use ListNamedQueries to get the list of named query IDs. If information could not be retrieved for a submitted query ID, information about the query ID submitted is listed under UnprocessedNamedQueryId. Named queries are different from executed queries. Use BatchGetQueryExecution to get details about each unique query execution, and ListQueryExecutions to get a list of query execution IDs.
declarations.title: batchGetNamedQuery

declarations.comments: Returns the details of a single query execution or a list of up to 50 query executions, which you provide as an array of query execution ID strings. To get a list of query execution IDs, use ListQueryExecutions. Query executions are different from named (saved) queries. Use BatchGetNamedQuery to get details about named queries.

declarations.comments: Returns information about a single execution of a query. Each time a query executes, information about the query execution is saved with a unique ID.

declarations.comments: Returns the results of a single query execution specified by QueryExecutionId. This request does not execute the query but returns results. Use StartQueryExecution to run a query.

Stops a query execution.

For code samples using the AWS SDK for Java, see Examples and Code Samples in the Amazon Athena User Guide.

declarations.comments: Information about the columns in a query execution result.
declarations.title: ColumnInfo

declarations.comments: A piece of data (a field in the table).
declarations.title: Datum

declarations.comments: If query results are encrypted in Amazon S3, indicates the Amazon S3 encryption option used.
declarations.title: EncryptionConfiguration

declarations.comments: Indicates a platform issue, which may be due to a transient condition or outage.
declarations.title: InternalServerException

declarations.comments: Indicates that something is wrong with the input to the request. For example, a required parameter may be missing or out of range.
declarations.title: InvalidRequestException

declarations.comments: A query, where QueryString is the SQL query statements that comprise the query.
declarations.title: NamedQuery

declarations.comments: Information about a single instance of a query execution.
declarations.title: QueryExecution

declarations.comments: The database in which the query execution occurs.
declarations.title: QueryExecutionContext

declarations.comments: The amount of data scanned during the query execution and the amount of time that it took to execute.
declarations.title: QueryExecutionStatistics

declarations.comments: The completion date, current state, submission time, and state change reason (if applicable) for the query execution.
declarations.title: QueryExecutionStatus

declarations.comments: The location in Amazon S3 where query results are stored and the encryption option, if any, used for query results.
declarations.title: ResultConfiguration

declarations.comments: The metadata and rows that comprise a query result set. The metadata describes the column structure and data types.
declarations.title: ResultSet

declarations.comments: The metadata that describes the column structure and data types of a table of query results.
declarations.title: ResultSetMetadata

declarations.comments: The rows that comprise a query result table.
declarations.title: Row

declarations.comments: Indicates that the request was throttled.
declarations.title: TooManyRequestsException

declarations.comments: Information about a named query ID that could not be processed.
declarations.title: UnprocessedNamedQueryId

declarations.comments: Describes a query execution that failed to process.
